reviews.review: The movie was fun. It was dumb. It's broken. It plays out like a videogame. But it was fun for a generic action movie.
I really enjoyed it! Definitely a fitting end to the saga.
Great fun. The critics are wrong and bitter
Critics are wrong again.  This movie had heart, emotion, action, story.  Sure it felt fast paced compared to Last Jedi but it all worked together well.  Can’t wait to see again.

I’ve been critical of the sequel trilogy thus far, but Rise of Skywalker is my favorite of the new 3 by a mile. There are some clunky elements but they’re easy to look past for the film’s strengths. And it’s great to see Anthony Daniels’ C-3PO in such a major role. Go see it!

This movie is fantastic! Possibly the best Star Wars movie ever, at least the second-best! I completely disagree with almost everything that the critics are saying. The only thing I agree with is that a lot happens in the first half of the movie. Although, It's not really that rushed. A lot happens, but it still didn't seem to me like they were trying to cram in a bunch of stuff in. Also, all that stuff... is AWESOME!! There are so many surprises and amazing moments throughout the entire movie! The movie is also hilarious! This is the best ending ever for the Skywalker saga. They honor the original and prequel trilogies, while also ending the sequels. Fans of any of the trilogies (especially all of them) will love this movie. If you walk into the theater wanting to hate this movie, you will (you would for any movie). But if you walk in, ready to be amazed, you will be. May the force be with you, always.
A great way to end the saga
As a fan of Emperor Palpatine and the Skywalker saga this movie gave the newest trilogy a fitting end.
The force is strong with this one!!!

A messy end to the trilogy which is so full of retconning the previous outing and adding exposition of its own that its pace is far too hectic for anything to have impact. 

The edit is all over the place, the dialogue clunky, even for Star Wars. 

The actors give great performances, however, and the effects are top notch. 

Just don't think too much about the story.

Edit after second viewing: I've given it a star more. After getting used to the hectic pace, there are still moments to be enjoyed even though they get little time to breathe. However, the main villain still makes little sense. 

Driver and Ridley are excellent. Some actors are unfortunately completely sidelined. 

The effects generally look good apart from some CGI faces which could be straight out of a video game. 

Ultimately, the movie is good but does not fulfill the potential that the previous installment or even Force Awakens set up for it.
